      "content": "To calculate your inventory turnover ratio, divide your cost of goods sold (COGS) by your average inventory value over the period. A low ratio typically indicates that you are selling your clothing stock slowly, which could mean you need to refresh your design selection, adjust pricing, or improve marketing. If this trend continues, you may face increased holding costs and reduced cash flow, so it’s a good time to audit your inventory levels and sales data.",
