      "content": "To determine if your stock is truly a problem, compare the inventory turnover ratio against industry benchmarks for your specific clothing niche and track the aging of your stock by looking at how long items have been in the back room. Signs of actual stock management failure include a consistently low turnover ratio, a growing number of \"slow-moving\" items, and a lack of regular inventory audits. Conversely, if your ratio dips only for a predictable period—like the off-season—and then recovers, it is likely a seasonal fluctuation rather than a systemic failure.",
